parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment or improper deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard is illuminated
the airbag warning indicator is on
the passenger airbag compartment is cracked
the dashboard is cracked around the airbag area
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag does not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can lead to the improper deployment of airbags, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities. Additionally, the cracking of the dashboard can cause sharp pieces of plastic to become projectiles in the event of an airbag deployment, further increasing the risk of injury.
symptoms: Cracks on the dashboard
cracks around the airbag area
cracks on the passenger side of the dashboard
cracks that are getting worse over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can lead to a safety concern, as it may compromise the integrity of the airbag system, potentially causing unintended airbag deployment or preventing proper deployment in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Cracks appearing on the dashboard
especially around the airbag area
which can spread rapidly and become more numerous over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls
the transmission slips or jerks
the vehicle loses power
the transmission makes a loud noise
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front axle can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front axle breaks or shears
the vehicle loses control
the vehicle is unable to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the dashboard can cause the airbag to deploy improperly, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The dashboard cracks or breaks
the airbag is exposed
